result.execSummary:
The defendant Brittney D. Eldridge was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
03:02 PM in Room 301. Defendant Brittney D. Eldridge in court with attorney John Zich.  Defendant Brittney D. Eldridge in custody at Langlade County Jail.  Elizabeth R. Gebert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Brittney D. Eldridge appeared by video means with Attorney. 20CF76 and 22CF29. Def. can hear and understand and consents to proceeding by Zoom. State indicates WOPH needed in 22CF29; information already filed in 20CF76.  State recites agreement. Def. to plead to 22CF29 - Ct. 1.  Ct. 2 and 3 to be DRI.  20CF76 - Def. to plead to Ct. 1 and 2. Ct. 3, 4 and 5 to be DRI.   Joint Recommendation:  20CF29 Ct. 1 -  1 year jail, imp/stayed, consec, 3 years probation, costs with DNA surcharge, sample, AODA and followthru, maintain abs. sobr., fulltime emp, letter of apology to victim, no restitution requested, counseling as deemed necessary.   76: Ct. 1 - imp/stayed 6 years prison (3 years ic, 3 years es), consec, 3 year probation, costs with DNA surcharge, comply with conditions.  Ct. 2 - withhold sentence, 3 years probation, costs with DNA surcharge, comply with conditions. State has complied with victim rights.   Attny Zich concurs. Def. seeks clarification in agreement; accepts agreement. 22CF29:  Waiver of prelim reviewed. Def. waives P.H. Court accepts waiver, finds probable cause and binds over for filing of Information. Attny Zich has not received copy but on representation Information mirrors criminal complaint, willing to proceed to plea/sentencing. Waives reading.  Plea questionnaire reviewed.  22CF29: Def. pleads to Ct. 1 - Bail jumping, repeater, no contest.  20CF76: Def. pleads to Ct. 1-Burglary, repeater, no contest; Ct. 2 - Poss of meth, repeater, no contest. Court grants State's motion to DRI Cts. 2 and 3 in 22CF29 and Cts. 3, 4 and 5 in 20CF76. Constitutional rights, elements and possible penalties reviewed. Attny Zich is satisfied. Court finds that Def. understands and that pleas are freely and voluntarily given. Court finds there is factual basis, accepts pleas and finds Def. guilty of Ct. 1 in 22CF29 and Ct. 1 and Ct. 2 in 20CF76. Sentencing argument by State. Sentencing remarks by Attny Zich. Def. has nothing to say. Remarks by the Court.
The Court will follow agreement, orders 
20CF76: Ct. 1 - imp/stayed 6 years prison (3 years init. conf., 3 yrs ext. sup.), 3 years probation, costs only including DNA surcharge, AODA and followthru, maintain absolute sobriety, maintain fulltime employment 30/hours week or apply for at least 5 jobs/week qualified for, letter of apology to victim, participate in any counseling as deemed beneficial by agent. Ct. 2 - withhold sentence, 3 years probation, costs only including DNA surcharge, same conditions of probation.
20CF29:    Ct. 1 -  imposed/stayed 1 year jail, Huber,  3 years probation, costs with DNA surcharge, same conditions of probation.  Court orders that Cts. 1 in both cases are consecutive to one another and consecutive to any other prior sentences. 
$1,000 cash bond in 20CF76 to be put toward costs; balance to be paid during probation.   22CF29: Costs to be paid during probation.
Credit:  19 days if revoked in 22CF29; 75 days if revoked in 20CF76.
If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. Eligible for earned release program and challenge incarceration programs. Firearm/voting rights. Post conviction rights.

01:14 PM Defendant Brittney D. Eldridge in court, in custody.  Elizabeth R. Gebert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Brittney D. Eldridge appeared by video means. All parties via Zoom. Def. is advised of charges and penalties.  Def. given atty rights and given 3 options, PD, hire own or court appointed atty. Defendant wishes to have council. DA gives bail bond argument and gives recommendation. Defendant gives response. $1,000 cash bond previously. DA recommends $2,000 cash bond. With conditions of no illegal use or possession of controlled substances without a valid prescription. Defendant gives response. Court gives ruling. Court rules $2,000 cash bond and conditions of no illegal use or possession of controlled substances without a valid prescription. Court is adjourned.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for March 7, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
